    <question number="6">
        <prompt>What role did the Homestead Strike of 1892 play in labor history?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Demonstrated the power of companies to crush unions</option>
            <option letter="b">Led to improved worker conditions</option>
            <option letter="c">Created new labor laws</option>
            <option letter="d">United all workers nationwide</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Homestead Strike showed how companies could use private security forces and state militia to defeat unions, marking a major setback for the labor movement.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question number="7">
        <prompt>What was the primary purpose of the Interstate Commerce Act of 1887?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To regulate railroad rates and practices</option>
            <option letter="b">To promote railroad construction</option>
            <option letter="c">To nationalize railroads</option>
            <option letter="d">To protect railroad owners</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Interstate Commerce Act was the first federal law to regulate private industry, specifically targeting unfair railroad rates and practices.</explanation>
